in%20the%20world%20of%20work.%20It%20does%20not%20matter%20what%20sector%20you're%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c84a18cf-e5f0-4252-977f-c7395ee79965%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20OK%20to%20say%20you%20were%20laid%20off%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EToothacre%20said%20that%2C%20unlike%20in%20the%20past%2C%20it's%20generally%20not%20as%20detrimental%20to%20be%20up%20front%20about%20a%20work%20drought%20on%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20That%20doesn't%20mean%20some%20people%20in%20charge%20of%20hiring%20won't%20ding%20applicants%20for%20it.%20But%20she%20said%20that%20itself%20can%20be%20a%20useful%20red%20flag%20for%20job%20seekers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20that's%20a%20situation%20that%20you're%20in%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20work%20for%20that%20person%20anyway%2C%26quot%3B%20Toothacre%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20recommends%20that%20if%20you%20were%20laid%20off%2C%20note%20that%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%20Or%2C%20she%20said%2C%20you%20could%20add%20a%20section%20that%20talks%20about%20being%20off%20work%20for%20personal%20reasons%20like%20having%20to%20care%20for%20someone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20the%20grounds%20for%20the%20break%2C%20it%20can%20be%20wise%20to%20be%20somewhat%20circumspect%2C%20she%20said.%20If%20you%20were%20off%20because%20of%20a%20protracted%20illness%2C%20it%20might%20be%20smart%20not%20to%20go%20too%20deep%20into%20it.%20Even%20though%20employers%20shouldn't%20discriminate%20against%20people%20for%2C%20say%2C%20having%20young%20kids%20who%20need%20attention%2C%20it%20can%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Toothacre%20said%20the%20decision%20by%20LinkedIn%20to%20let%20users%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-feature-lets-people-explain-career-gaps-13-ways-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadd%20a%20career%20break%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20their%20profile%20has%20helped%20normalize%20the%20idea%20that%20not%20all%20formal%20work%20unfolds%20without%20interruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESalemi%2C%20from%20Monster%2C%20said%20in%20her%20experience%20more%20job%20seekers%20have%20gaps%20than%20don't.%20And%20many%20people%20tend%20to%20overthink%20how%20to%20address%20them%2C%20she%20said.%20Her%20advice%20is%20to%20be%20prepared%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20breaks%20%E2%80%94%20and%20use%20that%20explanation%20to%20move%20the%20conversation%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20for%20workers%20who%20were%20fired%2C%20they%20could%20say%20something%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20the%20last%20one%20in%2C%20first%20one%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Salemi%20said.%20Then%20comes%20the%20pivot.%20One%20example%20she%20offered%3A%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20past%20three%20months%20really%20gave%20me%20clarity%20for%20this%20job%20I'm%20pursuing%20because%20my%20strengths%20are%20in%20sales%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221e4c3e69-a763-4a39-8b32-14bddc0fed0f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20dwell%20on%20the%20gap%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESalemi%20said%20the%20key%20is%20to%20address%20the%20hiatus%20so%20an%20interviewer%20doesn't%20get%20stuck%20on%20it.%20For%20those%20who%20might%20have%20done%20something%20like%20get%20additional%20education%2C%20build%20their%20skills%2C%20or%20work%20on%20a%20side%20hustle%2C%20it%20can%20be%20OK%20or%20even%20beneficial%20to%20talk%20about%20it%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20ways%20job%20seekers%20can%20downplay%20fallow%20spots%20in%20their%20formal%20work%20history.%20One%20is%20to%20perhaps%20not%20list%20start%20dates%20and%20end%20dates%20using%20months.%20Instead%2C%20Salemi%20said%2C%20consider%20using%20only%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20technique%20is%20to%20position%20the%20skills%20up%20top%20instead%20of%20first%20listing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthis-method-may-help-resume-stand-out-recruiter-job-search-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20history%20in%20reverse%20chronological%3