%20US%20Investing%20Championship%20with%20an%20805%25%20gain.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20watches%20for%20five%20patterns%20that%20he%20likes%20to%20trade.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20intraday%20VCP%20pattern%20involves%20price%20contractions%20and%20volume%20decreases%20before%20a%20breakout.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETrading%20strategies%20can%20be%20as%20unique%20as%20fingerprints.%20The%20approaches%20taught%20by%20coaches%20and%20other%20traders%20aren't%20always%20transplanted%20as%20is.%20Students%20often%20take%20tips%20and%20ideas%20from%20a%20thesis%20or%20pattern%20and%20integrate%20them%20into%20their%20own%20strategies%2C%20building%20a%20set%20of%20repeatable%20trades%20and%20signals%20to%20inform%20their%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-chart-indicators-trader-volatile-stocks-high-returns-in-2023-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoverdhan%20Gajjala%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%2044-year-old%2C%20Dallas-based%20software%20consultant%2C%20did%20while%20refining%20his%20trading%20strategy.%20He%20began%20as%20a%20swing%20trader%2C%20holding%20for%20days%20to%20a%20few%20months%20at%20a%20time%20%E2%80%94%20but%20gradually%20refined%20his%20approach%20to%20become%20a%20day%20trader.%20The%20switch%20made%20him%20feel%20more%20in%20control%20when%20entering%20and%20exiting%20trades%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGajjala%20had%20taken%20an%20online%20course%20with%20Mark%20Minervini%2C%20a%20veteran%20trader%20and%20a%20past%20winner%20of%20the%20US%20Investing%20Championship%2C%20where%20he%20learned%20how%20to%20tame%20his%20emotions%20and%20trade%20using%20a%20set%20of%20rules.%20In%202023%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20test%20his%20skills%20in%20the%20competition%20his%20coach%20had%20previously%20won.%20According%20to%20the%20competition%20founder%2C%20Norman%20Zadeh%2C%20Gajjala%20finished%20first%20in%20the%20stock%20division%20for%20those%20trading%20with%20more%20than%20%2420%2C000%2C%20with%20gains%20of%20805%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGajjala%20trades%20about%20five%20patterns%2C%20two%20of%20which%20he%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%20in%20previous%20interviews%3A%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpattern-day-trader-how-to-trade-chart-signals-stocks-reversals-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20reversal%20squeeze%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-trade-stocks-volatile-small-cap-penny-day-trader-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20bull%20flag%3C%2Fa%3E%20pullback.%20The%20third%20pattern%20he%20looks%20for%2C%20which%20he%20picked%20up%20from%20Minervini%2C%20is%20the%20volatility%20contraction%20pattern%20(VCP).%20It%20represents%20price%20action%20that%20tightens%20as%20it%20moves%20from%20left%20to%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22437d3f8e-3db5-45e6-8eb4-3a58e914c89c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIntraday%20VCP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20VCP%20pattern%20can%20be%20spotted%20over%20multiple%20days%20or%20weeks.%20But%20Gajjala%20uses%20it%20for%20day%20trades%2C%20which%20can%20last%2030%20minutes%20to%20an%20hour.%20He%20refers%20to%20it%20as%20an%20intraday%20VCP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20sign%20of%20the%20pattern%20begins%20with%20an%20initial%20spike%20in%20price%20or%20the%20first%20move%20up.%20A%20series%20of%20smaller%20sell-offs%20or%20pullbacks%20then%20follow%20it.%20If%20it%20develops%20into%20a%20VCP%2C%20the%20volatility%20will%20decrease%20in%20a%20gradual%20upward-moving%20pattern%20as%20it%20continues%20to%20find%20support%20at%20the%2021-day%20exponential%20moving%20average%20line%20on%20the%20five-minute%20chart.%20There%20are%20longer%20and%20shorter%20EMAs%20that%20can%20work%2C%20but%20for%20the%20period%20Gajjala%20is%20trading%20in%2C%20he%20found%20that%20the%2021-day%20option%20is%20the%20most%20consistent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20contraction%20pattern%20must%20be%20accompanied%20by%20decreasing%20volume%20bars%20after%20the%20initial%20and%20sudden%20increase%20in%20price.%20The%20spike%20in%20green%20volume%20bars%20parallel%20to%20the%20first%20price%20spike%20demonstrates%20this%20in%20the%20chart%20below.%20The%20pullback%20periods%20are%20then%20accompanied%20by%20weaker%20selling%20pressure%2C%20shown%20by%20shrinking%20red%20bars%20as%20the%20pattern%20moves%20to%20the%20right.%20This%20pattern%20will%20repeat%20itself%20until%20the%20selling%20pressure%20diminishes%20and%20the%20pullbacks%20become%20more%20shallow%2C%20narrowing%20price%20volatility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20contractions%20have%20tightened%20and%20the%20selling%20volume%20has%20diminished%2C%20it%20can%20be%20followed%20by%20a%20breakout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Gajjala%2C%20it's%20an%20easier%20pattern%20to%20trade%20because%20the%20contraction%20period%20is%20longer%20than%20other%20patterns%20he%20watches%20for.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20bull%20flag%20pullback%2C%20a%20spike%20in%20price%20that%20resembles%20a%20flag%20on%20the%20chart%2C%20can%20happen%20within%20seconds%20and%20as%20little%20as%20two%20to%20three%20candles.%20It%20gives%20him%20very%20little%20time%20to%20make%20a%20trading%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20VCP%2C%20he%20can%20watch%20it%20for%2030%20minutes%20to%20an%20hour%20as%20the%20volatility%20diminishes%20while%20the%20price%20gradually%20increases%20along%20the%2021-day%20EMA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20or%20less%20very%20clear%20and%20easy%20to%20identify%2C%26quot%3B%20Gajjala%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20volume%20profile%20will%20be%20so%20neat%2C%20and%20I'll%20have%20plenty%20of%20time%20to%20wait%20and%20watch%20this%20setup.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chart%20below%20is%20an%20example%20of%20an%20intraday%20VCP.%20It%20shows%20the%20initial%20spike%20in%20price%20accompanied%20by%20high%20demand%2C%20as%20demonstrated%20by%20the%20green%20volume%20bars.%20It's%20followed%20by%20tightening%20contractions%20and%20less%20volume.%20The%20%26quot%3Bentry%26quot%3B%20mark%20on%20the%20chart%20is%20where%20Gajjala%20tries%20to%20enter.%20Here%2C%20selling%20pressure%20has%20died%20down%2C%20and%20price%20volatility%20has%20eased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221320%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stock%20chart%20of%20a%20%20VCP%20pattern%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b67811955b01c3294d6e92%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22753%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EThinkorswim%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20danger%20of%20this%20setup%20is%20that%20a%20trader%20can%20be%20too%20early%20to%20the%20trade%20and%20the%20chances%20the%20pattern%20breaks%20up%20or%20down%20are%20the%20same%2C%20he%20noted.%20This%20means%20a%20trader%20must%20have%20more%20patience%20to%20play%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Gajjala%20first%20began%20trading%20the%20intraday%20VCP%2C%20he%20was%20unsuccessful%20because%20he%20would%20enter%20the%20trade%20before%20allowing%20the%20contractions%20to%20develop.%20He%20assumed%20getting%20in%20early%20would%20increase%20his%20gains%2C%20but%20the%20pattern%20would%20usually%20break%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20an%20example%20of%20a%20trade%20Gajjala%20took%20on%20Syntec%20Optics%20Holdings%20(OPTX)%20on%20November%2017.%20The%20stock's%20price%20spiked%20at%20the%20stock%20market%20open%2C%20followed%20by%20continued%20contraction%20and%20dropping%20volume%20by%2011%3A00%20a.m.%20According%20to%20his%20brokerage%20statement%2C%20he%20entered%20the%20trade%20buying%20about%2024%2C000%20shares%20between%20%247.07%20and%20%248.29%20and%20exited%20between%20%248.31%20and%20%248.61.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221425%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22OPTX%20stock%20chart%20VCP%20pattern%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66b67844955b01c3294d6eaa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22741%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EThinkorswim%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3