0the%20age%20of%2017%2C%20Walz%20enlisted%20in%20the%20Nebraska%20Army%20National%20Guard%2C%20where%20he%20served%20as%20an%20infantry%20senior%20sergeant%20and%20administrative%20specialist.%20In%201996%2C%20he%20transferred%20to%20the%20Minnesota%20National%20Guard%20and%20held%20various%20field%20artillery%20positions%2C%20including%20firing%20battery%20chief%2C%20operations%20sergeant%2C%20first%20sergeant%2C%20and%20command%20sergeant%20major.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202003%2C%20Walz%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.army.mil%2Farticle%2F234854%2Fonce_in_the_guard_always_ready_to_serve%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esent%20abroad%20as%20part%20of%20Operation%20Enduring%20Freedom%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20stage%20one%20of%20America's%20war%20on%20terror%2C%20which%20primarily%20took%20place%20in%20Afghanistan.%20He%20was%20on%20active%20duty%20in%20Italy%20until%202004%20but%20he%20never%20went%20to%20Afghanistan%20or%20Iraq.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecords%20show%20that%20Walz%20submitted%20paperwork%20with%20the%20Federal%20Elections%20Commission%20on%20February%2010%2C%202005.%20A%20month%20later%2C%20in%20March%202005%2C%20the%20National%20Guard%20announced%20the%20potential%20partial%20mobilization%20of%20troops%20from%20the%20Minnesota%20National%20Guard.%20In%20a%20statement%20from%20that%20time%2C%20Walz%20said%20he%20didn't%20know%20if%20his%20artillery%20unit%20would%20be%20mobilized%20but%20said%20he%20did%20not%20intend%20to%20drop%20his%20election%20bid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20command%20sergeant%20major%20I%20have%20a%20responsibility%20not%20only%20to%20ready%20my%20battalion%20for%20Iraq%2C%20but%20also%20to%20serve%20if%20called%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20050420004957%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.timwalz.org%2Fpr.php%3Fpr%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20March%202005.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20dedicated%20to%20serving%20my%20country%20to%20t