%20one%20of%20the%20first%20Google%20employees%2C%20has%20died%20after%20a%20two-year%20battle%20with%20cancer.%20She%20was%2056.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20Facebook%2C%20Ms%20Wojcicki's%20husband%20Dennis%20Troper%20said%20that%20she%20was%20battling%20non-small%20cell%20lung%20cancer.%20%26quot%3BMy%20beloved%20wife%20of%2026%20years%20and%20mother%20to%20our%20five%20children%20left%20us%20today%20after%202%20years%20of%20living%20with%20non-small%20cell%20lung%20cancer.%20Susan%20was%20not%20just%20my%20best%20friend%20and%20partner%20in%20life%2C%20but%20a%20brilliant%20mind%2C%20a%20loving%20mother%2C%20and%20a%20dear%20friend%20to%20many%2C%26quot%3B%20Troper%20wrote%20alongside%20a%20few%20family%20photographs.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnHe%20noted%20that%20her%20impact%20on%20the%20family%20and%20the%20world%20was%20%26quot%3Bimmeasurable.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fplugins%2Fpost.php%3Fhref%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.facebook.com%252Fdtroper%252Fposts%252Fpfbid035AsHMEC3xs1EyqrDWHVBmeVJq6sXXJaGUF5RQH962SxK3zYyihDDhWiza9epUdKTl%26show_text%3Dtrue%26width%3D500%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22250%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cstrong%3EWho%20was%20Susan%20Wojcicki%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn1.%20Born%20on%20July%205%2C%201968%2C%20in%20Santa%20Clara%2C%20California%2C%20she%20was%20the%20daughter%20of%20Stanley%2C%20who%20taught%20physics%20at%20Stanford%20University.%20Her%20mother%20Esther%20worked%20as%20a%20journalist%20and%20teacher%20at%20the%20Palo%20Alto%20High%20School%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn2.%20Ms%20Wojcicki%20studied%20history%20at%20Harvard%20University%20and%20later%20worked%20as%20a%20photojournalist%20in%20India.%20Within%20a%20few%20years%2C%20she%20returned%20to%20California%20to%20receive%20advanced%20degrees%20in%20economics%20and%20business.%20Later%20on%2C%20she%20took%20up%20a%20marketing%20role%20with%20Intel%20Corp.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn3.%20In%201998%2C%20when%20Google%20co-founders%20Larry%20Page%20and%20Sergey%20Brin%20incorporated%20the%20search%20engine%20into%20a%20business%2C%20Ms%20Wojcicki%20rented%20the%20garage%20of%20her%20home%20in%20Menlo%20Park%2C%20California%2C%20to%20them%20for%20%241%2C700%20a%20month.%20After%20working%20there%20for%20a%20few%20months%2C%20they%20later%20moved%20Google%20into%20a%20more%20formal%20office.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn4.%20She%20was%20hired%20in%201999%20as%20the%2016th%20employee%20of%20Google%20and%20later%20went%20on%20to%20work%20towards%20everything%20from%20AdSense%2C%20Google%20Analytics%20and%20Google%20Books%20to%20Google%20Images.%20In%202006%2C%20the%20company%20bought%20her%20home%20to%20serve%20as%20a%20monument%20to%20its%20roots.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Brin%20became%20her%20brother-in-law%20and%20married%20her%20sister%2C%20Anne%2C%20in%202007.%20However%2C%20the%20former%20couple%20parted%20ways%20in%202015.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn5.%20Wojcicki%20had%20in%202006%20advocated%20for%20the%20%241.65%20billion%20acquisition%20of%20YouTube.%20Being%20its%20CEO%2C%20she%20went%20on%20to%20expand%20its%20viewership%20to%202.5%20billion%20monthly%20users.%20In%20February%202023%2C%20Ms%20Wojcicki%20announced%20her%20decision%20to%20step%20down%20as%20YouTube's%20CEO%20after%20spending%20around%20nine%20years%20of%20being%20the%20front%20and%20centre%20of%20the%20company.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnFrom%20being%20one%20of%20the%20early%20employees%20of%20Google%20who%20helped%20jumpstart%20the%20company%20in%20her%20garage%20to%20running%20the%20tech%20giant's%20advertising%20business%20and%20then%20YouTube%20for%20most%20of%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Wojcicki%20has%20had%20a%20journey%20of%20a%20lifetime.%20Ms%20Wojcicki%20married%20Dennis%20Troper%2C%20who%20was%20a%20fellow%20veteran%20Google%20manager%2C%20back%20in%201998.%20In%20February%20this%20year%2C%20one%20of%2