t%20her%20French%20opponent%20of%20Indian%20origin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20securing%20the%20title%20of%20the%20first%20Indian%20table%20tennis%20player%20to%20reach%20Olympics%20pre-quarterfinals%2C%20Manika%20reflected%20through%20a%20post%20on%20Instagram%2C%20%E2%80%9CReaching%20the%20pre-quarterfinals%20of%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Singles%20in%20Olympics%20has%20been%20a%20milestone%2C%20but%20I%20always%20want%20more.%20As%20long%20as%20I%20have%20a%20dream%2C%20an%20aim%2C%20I%20will%20keep%20doing%20my%20best.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2029-year-old%20hails%20from%20Delhi%20and%20is%20the%20youngest%20of%20three%20siblings.%20At%20the%20young%20age%20of%20four%2C%20she%20was%20introduced%20to%20the%20sport%20by%20her%20sister%2C%20Aanchal%2C%20and%20brother%20Sahil%2C%20both%20of%20whom%20also%20played%20table%20tennis.%20It%20became%20clear%20that%20she%20was%20destined%20for%20greatness%20when%20she%20won%20a%20state-level%20under-8%20tournament%2C%20prompting%20her%20to%20train%20under%20coach%20Sandeep%20Gupta%20at%20Hans%20Raj%20Model%20School.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManika%E2%80%99s%20rise%20to%20fame%20began%20with%20a%20silver%20medal%20in%20the%20under-21%20category%20at%20the%202011%20Chile%20Open.%20She%20also%20achieved%20quarterfinal%20finishes%20while%20representing%20India%20at%20the%202014%20Commonwealth%20Games%20in%20Glasgow%20and%20the%202014%20Asian%20Games.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20breakthrough%20arrived%20at%20the%202015%20Commonwealth%20Table%20Tennis%20Championships%2C%20where%20she%20won%20three%20medals%2C%20including%20silver%20in%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20team%20and%20doubles%20events%20and%20bronze%20in%20singles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20her%20achievements%2C%20Manika%20grew%20up%20hearing%2C%20%E2%80%9CTable%20tennis%20is%20a%20waste%20of%20time%2C%20be%20a%20doctor%20or%20engineer%20instead.%E2%80%9D%20Growing%20up%20in%20Delhi%2C%20her%20relatives%20taunted%20her%20for%20choosing%20sports%20as%20a%2